    "assessment": "No strong evidence for universal mathematical power law constants. The exponents span a wide range (0.2 to 2.9) and cluster weakly. The strongest pattern is a cluster near alpha~1.4-1.5 spanning EC Tamagawa products, modular degree scaling, naive height scaling, and Fungrim clique sizes \u2014 but these arise from different mechanisms. Graph degree exponents (1.3-2.6) reflect network topology, not intrinsic arithmetic. The ~0.5 cluster (Fourier growth, genus-2 scaling, lattice theta) likely reflects underlying Ramanujan-type bounds (theoretical alpha=0.5 for weight-2 forms). Cross-domain coincidences exist but lack explanatory power \u2014 same exponent does not imply same mechanism."
  },
